The paper deals with the degrees of freedom of a communication channel, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of coordinated multipoint transmission and reception is a technique commonly used in wireless networks (cs.NI). The paper also mentions the use of asymptotic interference alignment, which is a technique used in signal processing and communication systems (cs.SI). The paper proposes a coding scheme, which involves canceling interference and using algebraic independence, both of which are techniques used in coding theory (cs.MM). Finally, the paper uses algebraic geometry to prove the achievability of the proposed scheme, which falls under the category of computational geometry and topology (cs.DS).
